│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                                                                                                 │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                                                                                                     │
│ The function foldSelectOfBools transforms a boolean select into a logical and/or form and then defers to foldBooleanAndOr, which calls foldAndOrOfICmps with    │
│ IsLogical=true. This is meant to ensure poison-safety (short-circuit semantics) when folding select-of-bools. However, foldAndOrOfICmps internally invokes a    │
│ "swapped" transform foldAndOrOfICmpEqConstantAndICmp(RHS, LHS, ..., IsLogical=false) that treats the logical operation as if it were a bitwise one and commutes │
│ operands. This can drop the original guard/short-circuit order and produce a result that uses only the RHS compare (e.g., icmp samesign), which can be poison   │
│ even when the original select would have short-circuited.                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ In the reproducer:                                                                                                                                              │
│   %cmp1 = icmp samesign eq i8 %x, -1                                                                                                                            │
│   %cmp2 = icmp ne i8 %x, 0                                                                                                                                      │
│   %result = select i1 %cmp2, i1 %cmp1, i1 false                                                                                                                 │
│ InstCombine replaced the select with %cmp1, which is poison when %x == 0. The original select is well-defined (false) when %x == 0 because it does not evaluate │
│ the true arm. Alive2 shows the transform is incorrect: target more poisonous than source.                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                                                                                                         │
│ - The first transformation replaces the select directly with %cmp1 in foldSelectOfBools (InstCombineSelect.cpp:3368).                                           │
│ - The decision comes from the foldBooleanAndOr path: it tries to fold select B ? C : false into B && C with IsLogical=true and then into just C due to an       │
│ internal transform in foldAndOrOfICmps that swapped operands and simplified the RHS-side compare and constant to just the RHS compare.                          │
│ - No samesign-drop occurred (final IR still shows "icmp samesign eq"), so poison remained.                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                                                                                         │
│ - foldAndOrOfICmps, when IsLogical is true, still invokes a swapped direction transform using IsLogical=false:                                                  │
│   if (Value *V = foldAndOrOfICmpEqConstantAndICmp(RHS, LHS, IsAnd, /*IsLogical=*/false, ...)) return V;                                                         │
│ - This breaks poison-safety: logical and/or is not commutative w.r.t. poison because the first operand determines short-circuiting and whether a potentially    │
│ poison RHS is used. Swapping can cause a previously RHS poison value (like icmp samesign) to be evaluated first and then simplified to itself, eliminating the  │
│ original guard and reintroducing poison. The ad-hoc attempt to drop samesign on RHS does not always trigger (and even if it did, the reordering is still        │
│ dangerous since other poison forms may exist).                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                                                                                                       │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp                                                                                                 │
│ - Location: In InstCombinerImpl::foldAndOrOfICmps, around the second call to foldAndOrOfICmpEqConstantAndICmp with swapped operands.                            │
│ - Change: Do not perform the swapped-direction transform when IsLogical is true. This preserves the original short-circuit order and avoids turning a logical   │
│ select form into an expression that evaluates the poison-producing comparison first or drops the guard entirely.                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Edit:                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Replace the block:                                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│   if (Value *V = foldAndOrOfICmpEqConstantAndICmp(RHS, LHS, IsAnd,                                                                                              │
│                                                   /*IsLogical*/ false, Builder)) {                                                                              │
│     // If RHS is still used, we should drop samesign flag.                                                                                                      │
│     if (IsLogical && RHS->hasSameSign() && !RHS->use_empty()) {                                                                                                 │
│       RHS->setSameSign(false);                                                                                                                                  │
│       addToWorklist(RHS);                                                                                                                                       │
│     }                                                                                                                                                           │
│     return V;                                                                                                                                                   │
│   }                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ with:                                                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│   if (!IsLogical)                                                                                                                                               │
│     if (Value *V = foldAndOrOfICmpEqConstantAndICmp(RHS, LHS, IsAnd,                                                                                            │
│                                                     /*IsLogical*/ false, Builder))                                                                              │
│       return V;                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Rationale:                                                                                                                                                      │
│ - When IsLogical is true (folding a select-of-bools), we must preserve short-circuit semantics and must not commute operands or introduce bitwise operations    │
│ that could change which side is evaluated first. Skipping the swapped-direction transform in the logical context prevents the observed miscompile.              │
│ - We also remove the special-case samesign drop in that block, as it would no longer execute in the logical context and is unnecessary in the preserved         │
│ bitwise-only path.                                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The bug stems from treating logical (select) boolean folding as bitwise in a swapped direction, which can reorder operands and eliminate the guard that         │
│ protected against poison (e.g., icmp samesign). By disabling the swapped-direction transform when IsLogical is true, we prevent reordering and ensure that      │
│ transforms remain poison-safe. The select will no longer be incorrectly replaced by the poison-producing compare, fixing the Alive2 failure and maintaining     │
│ correctness.                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                                                                                                 │
